-- Consob Chief Cardia to Be Appointed Italian Railways Chief, Corriere Says
-- Lorenzo Totaro
-- 2010-06-25T05:51:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/consob-chief-cardia-to-be-appointed-italian-railways-chief-corriere-says.html

          
          
             Lamberto Cardia , chairman of Italy’s
securities market regulator Consob, may be appointed chairman of
Ferrovie dello Stato SpA, the country’s railway company,
Corriere della Sera reported without saying where it got the
information.  
 Mauro Moretti  will stay as chief executive officer of
Ferrovie dello Stato, the Milan-based newspaper said.  Antonio Catricala , head of Italy’s antitrust authority, may replace
Cardia as head of Consob, Corriere said.  
